snippet.textDisplay:
I don't understand why an EV is competing with combustion engine cars.

An EV is just a giant battery with a mould of a car shell covering them.

The super cars (minus the silly EV) are a work of art! Their sound, particularly the AMG are beautiful to listen too. They are engineered to near perfection cosmetically and mechanically.

The EV on the other is a bulk of a vehicle that the only engineered part of it is a giant like Duracell battery. No beautiful V8/V10 power once launched to listen too, just silence!! What's the point of ownership of an EV??
